- content_for(:title, 'The Theory')
%p BipolarType defines four realms of behavior, each of which revolves around a different kind of energy. Each realm has behaviors which achieve goals (energy out) and other behaviors which harvest resources (energy in).
%table
  %caption.heading The Four Realms
  %tr
    %th.narrow
    -Realm.each do |realm|
      %th=link_to realm.name, realm_path(realm.path)
  -%w{energy goals resources}.each do |word|
    %tr
      %th=word.titleize
      -Realm.each do |realm|
        %td=realm.send(word)
%p Balance is achieved when energy out equals energy in. Short term energy deficits or surpluses are possible, but in the long run an equilibirum must be established.
%table
  %caption.heading The Four Attitudes
  %tr
    %th.narrow
    -Attitude.each do |attitude|
      %th=link_to attitude.name, attitude_path(attitude.path)
  -%w{imbalance solution}.each do |word|
    %tr
      %th=word.titleize
      -Attitude.each do |attitude|
        %td=attitude.send(word)
%p A BipolarType is the four attitudes distributed over the four realms: one realm for each attitude.
